Alright, letâ€™s create an AI prototype that combines singing and music generation capabilities! We'll take things step by step to build something magical.

Step 1: Choose Libraries and Models
For this prototype, weâ€™ll use:

TTS Models for Singing:

Google Tacotron 2 + WaveNet: High-quality voice synthesis with some tunable singing capabilities.

Sunoâ€™s Bark (optional): An experimental generative model capable of expressive speech and singing. You can explore Bark on Hugging Face.

Music Generation Models:

Google Magenta (for melodies and rhythms): Great for generating MIDI music sequences.

OpenAI Jukebox: Advanced AI for creating music with lyrics and vocals.

Step 2: Set Up the Environment
